Statoil Reserve Recovery May Top 100% in ‘Couple of Years’

-- B y   M o m i n g   Z h o u
-- 
2011-06-20T12:31:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/statoil-reserve-recovery-may-top-100-in-couple-of-years-1-.html
Statoil ASA (STL) ’s reserve recovery rate
will rise above 100 percent in the “next couple of years,”
Chief Executive Officer  Helge Lund  told reporters in New York
today. The rate is currently about 87 percent.  Statoil will focus on developing shale gas in North
America, particularly in the Marcellus and Eagle Ford deposits,
Lund said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
